An MKV file is a Matroska video file which is just another video file format. You may need to download a different video codec to play it but it works fine. VLC player is a great player that I have never needed to update additional codecs for, and many highly recommend it. IF you want a codec pack, try http://www.cccp-project.net/ , the Combined Community Codec Pack. It's great and last time i had to dl it, it came with an assortment of players as well. 

As for the 'lip syncing'... this is a dub of a Swedish film so things won't be perfect. If you don't like reading along with the speaking, then settle for the dub.
